RATTET--Elaine, H. On January 3rd, 2007, beloved wife of Robert, adored mother of Michael, cherished sister of the late Carol Lefcourt, survived by Jenny, Daniel, and Megan Lefcourt, and Kim, Melissa, Seth Rattet, and their children. Noted ceramicist. Donation to Doctors Cancer Foundation, PO Box 73 Wykagyl Station, New Rochelle, NY 10804, or Elaine Rattet Fellowship at The Clay Art Center, 40 Beach St., Port Chester, NY 10573. Services Sunday 10 am at Riverside Memorial Chapel, 21 W Broad St., Mount Vernon, NY.
RATTET--Elaine. The Board of Governors and members of Willow Ridge Country Club sadly note the passing of Elaine Rattet, a distinguished and beloved member of this club. Our deepest condolences are offered to her husband Robert Rattet and to their family. Dr. Alan Schrager, President Board of Governors
RATTET--Elaine. The attournies and staff of Rattet, Pasternak, & Gordon Oliver, LLP, mourn the untimely passing of Elaine Rattet, beloved wife of our senior partner Bob Rattet. Her warm smile and her laugh are forever etched in our minds. May she rest in peace. Attournies and staff of Rattet, Pasternak, & Gordon Oliver LLP
